<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
     <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/index.css" />
    <title>The Bicycle Shop</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <nav>
        <header>
          <h1>The Bicycle Shop</h1>
        </header>
      </nav>
      <div class="singleBicycle">
        <div class="singleBicycle_img">
          <img src="/images/<%=myBicycle.image%>" alt="<%=myBicycle.name%>" />
        </div>
        <div class="singleBicycle_info">
          <div class="singleBicycle_name">
            <p><%=myBicycle.name%></p>
          </div>

          <div class="singleBicycle_price">
            <p>R<% if(myBicycle.hasDiscount) { %>
              <%=myBicycle.originalPrice - (myBicycle.originalPrice * (myBicycle.discount / 100))%>
              <%  } else { %>
                <%=myBicycle.originalPrice%>

                <%}%>
          </p>
          </div>

          <div class="singleBicycle_desc">
            <p>
              Remember the freedom, fun, and sense of accomplishment that your
              first bike gave you? Well, these days, kids can get rolling at an
              even earlier age with toddler-friendly walk bikes and
              coaster-brake-equipped 20-inch models that are ideal for
              neighborhood adventures. Even better, the fun of our kids bikes is
              equally matched with the quality and value that parents appreciate
              <br />
